---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Disclaimer from '../components/Disclaimer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — LegalAI CA"
  description="Privacy Policy for LegalAI CA. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your information when you visit our California legal information website."
  canonical="/privacy"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', url: 'https://legalai-ca.top/' },
    { name: 'Privacy Policy', url: 'https://legalai-ca.top/privacy' },
  ]}
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: May 28, 2026</p>

    <div class="prose max-w-none">
      <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        LegalAI CA ("we," "our," or "us") respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy
        explains how we collect, use, and protect information when you visit
        <strong>legalai-ca.top</strong> (the "Site").
      </p>
      <p>
        We are committed to transparency about our data practices and compliance with
        applicable privacy laws, including the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)
        and the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) where applicable.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>2.1 No Tracking or Cookies (Currently)</h3>
      <p>
        As of the date above, LegalAI CA does <strong>not</strong> use cookies, web
        beacons, or any form of user tracking. We do not collect, store, or process
        any personal information about visitors. The site is designed to be fully
        functional without any data collection.
      </p>

      <h3>2.2 Server Logs (Standard)</h3>
      <p>
        Our hosting provider (Cloudflare) automatically collects standard server log
        information, which may include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>IP address (anonymized by Cloudflare)</li>
        <li>Browser type and version</li>
        <li>Pages visited and timestamps</li>
        <li>Referring website addresses</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This data is used solely for site security, performance optimization, and
        diagnostics. It is not used for user profiling or behavioral analysis.
      </p>

      <h3>2.3 AI Assistant</h3>
      <p>
        When you use our AI Legal Assistant, your questions are sent to our server
        and processed by a third-party AI provider (DeepSeek). We do <strong>not</strong>
        store chat histories server-side. Your messages are processed in real-time
        and not retained after the response is delivered. Do not submit confidential
        or sensitive information through the AI assistant.
      </p>

      <h3>2.4 Future: Google AdSense</h3>
      <p>
        We may display advertisements via Google AdSense in the future. When activated,
        Google AdSense may use cookies and web beacons to serve personalized ads
        based on your visits to this and other websites. You can learn more about
        Google's advertising practices at
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Google's Partner Sites Policy
        </a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        If and when AdSense is enabled, we will update this Privacy Policy accordingly
        and provide appropriate cookie consent mechanisms.
      </p>

      <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>Any information we collect is used only for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Operating and maintaining the Site</li>
        <li>Improving user experience and site performance</li>
        <li>Diagnosing technical issues and enhancing security</li>
        <li>Complying with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or share personal information with third parties for marketing purposes.</p>

      <h2>4. Data Storage and Security</h2>
      <p>
        We implement reasonable security measures to protect against unauthorized
        access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction of information. All data
        transmission between your browser and our servers is encrypted using TLS/SSL.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>We use the following third-party services:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloudflare</strong> — CDN and hosting. Cloudflare's privacy policy
          is available at
          <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            cloudflare.com/privacypolicy
          </a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>DeepSeek</strong> — AI processing for the Legal Assistant. DeepSeek's
          privacy policy is available at
          <a href="https://platform.deepseek.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            platform.deepseek.com/privacy
          </a>.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Your California Privacy Rights (CCPA)</h2>
      <p>
        As a California-based website, we respect the rights granted to California
        residents under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA). Under the CCPA,
        you have the right to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Know</strong> what personal information is collected about you</li>
        <li><strong>Request deletion</strong> of personal information we hold</li>
        <li><strong>Opt out</strong> of the sale of personal information (we do not sell data)</li>
        <li><strong>Non-discrimination</strong> for exercising your CCPA rights</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Currently, we do not collect personal information that would trigger CCPA
        obligations. If our data practices change in the future, we will update this
        policy and provide appropriate notice.
      </p>
      <p>
        To exercise your CCPA rights, contact us at the email address below.
        We will respond within 45 days as required by law.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        This Site is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not
        knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe
        a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and we
        will take steps to delete such information.
      </p>

      <h2>8. International Users</h2>
      <p>
        This Site is hosted in the United States and is intended for users in the
        United States, specifically California. If you access the Site from outside
        the United States, you acknowledge that your information may be transferred
        to and processed in the United States.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time. Changes will
        be posted on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. We encourage you
        to review this policy periodically.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy,
        please contact us at:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Email:</strong> contact@legalai-ca.top
      </p>
    </div>

    <hr class="my-8 border-border" />
    <Disclaimer />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
